        <h1>Documentation: Customer and Item Pricing</h1>
        
        <section class="overview">
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>This application tracks and manages customer purchases and item pricing. It calculates special prices based on customer-item combinations and stores these details in a PostgreSQL database. The system also provides an interface to view these prices and calculate totals for customers.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="combinations">
            <h2>1. Customer and Item Combinations</h2>
            
            <h3>1.1. Customers</h3>
            <p>The application supports the following customers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Customer 1:</strong> Identified as "one"</li>
                <li><strong>Customer 2:</strong> Identified as "two"</li>
                <li><strong>Customer 3:</strong> Identified as "three"</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>1.2. Items</h3>
            <p>The available items are:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Item A</li>
                <li>Item B</li>
                <li>Item C</li>
                <li>Item D</li>
                <li>Item E</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section class="pricing-rules">
            <h2>2. Special Pricing Rules</h2>
            <p>The special pricing is applied based on the combination of customer and item. The following rules determine the special price for each combination:</p>
            
